Job Details - Experienced Maths Teachers Required in Dubai
Experienced Maths Teachers Required in Dubai
Donderdag 1 mei 2014
Description
This school is a member of BSME and MEIBA and is at the heart of the community catering for more than 900 international students from across 80 countries and is supported by an exceptional team who offer warmth, support and encouragement which allows students to develop into responsible life - long learners. Operating the IB MYP / DP and IGCSE curriculum , the school nurtures a communal spirit with parents, teachers and students working in partnership to develop self-esteem and individuality alongside high academic achievements.
This is a fantastic opportunity to join a forward thinking team which provides extensive development and training while working alongside professional international educators.
Applicant requirements: Bachelor's degree in Teaching Subject along with a relevant Teaching Certificate and 2 years solid teaching experience. Knowledge or practice of the IB MYP / DP or IGCSE curriculum is desirable along with being flexible, adaptable and passionate about teaching.
All degrees MUST have been issued in either UK,Ireland,Australia/New Zealand/Canada/US & South Africa ONLY.
A comprehensive package is offered with this position: Tax free salary, single occupancy furnished accommodation, annual flights, and medical insurance plus other benefits.
If you wish to apply for this position, please your local consultant, Katie from Teachanywhere on ks@Teachanywhere.com
Job Reference:Ks/Maths
Position Type:Permanent
Sector:Education, Training & Library
Location:Dubai, Dubai, United Arab Emirates
Contact:Katie Smith, Contact Code: Ks/Maths, Randstad, Teach Anywhere, Australia
